  <description type="morphology">Stems seldom branching; rounded in transverse section; rhizoids usually few.  Leaves ligulate to elliptic, apex acute or rounded acute and apiculate with an elongate, brownish, thick-walled cell, costa percurrent or subpercurrent; proximal laminal cells ca. 20–25 µm wide, 2–4:1.  Brood bodies sometimes present, borne on rhizoids in soil, clavate, ca. 100–130 µm.  Sporophytes not known from North America.</description>
  <description type="morphology">Found on bare soil in disturbed, open areas;</description>
